  "text": "Found 8 reference files in sg-evals/envoy--v1.31.2 showing the Envoy HTTP filter extension pattern. The core interfaces: (1) envoy/http/filter.h defines StreamDecoderFilter (decodeHeaders, decodeData, decodeTrailers pure virtual methods) and StreamFilter (combines decoder+encoder). (2) envoy/server/filter_config.h defines NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory (createFilterFactoryFromProto). (3) envoy/registry/registry.h provides the REGISTER_FACTORY macro for factory registration. (4) source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h provides FactoryBase<ConfigProto> and DualFactoryBase<ConfigProto> convenience templates. Reference implementation: the Buffer filter is the simplest decoder-only example. buffer_filter.h declares BufferFilter inheriting StreamDecoderFilter with decodeHeaders/decodeData/decodeTrailers/setDecoderFilterCallbacks/onDestroy. buffer_filter.cc implements the methods. config.h declares BufferFilterFactory inheriting DualFactoryBase. config.cc implements createFilterFactoryFromProtoTyped returning a lambda that calls callbacks.addStreamDecoderFilter(). Pattern: filter class inherits StreamDecoderFilter, factory inherits FactoryBase, config.cc uses REGISTER_FACTORY(Factory, NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory).",
